                        "node": {
                            "id": "238695705",
                            "title": "Coding with our favourite tech stacks ❤️",
                            "eventUrl": "https://www.meetup.com/mumbai-women-coders/events/238695705/",
                            "description": "https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/f/4/7/600_460448007.jpeg\n\nHey TechGeeks,\n\nWe're excited to bring to you our very first event in the last week of April, 2017. Come attend the meetup to witness the latest tech stack talks at Microsoft Office in Mumbai.\nIt's gonna be a fun session power-packed with immense knowledge. Watch us explore some of the cool technologies of today. We've awesome speakers, who'll make tech jargons easy for you to understand.\n\nFollowing topics will be covered in the session:\n\n1) Strengthening IT ecosystem via developer communities\n\nSpeaker Aditee Rele (Leads technical evangelism at @Microsoft)\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n2) TICK Stack - A complete solution to time series data management\n\n• What is time series data?\n\n• What is TICK?\n\n• Components of TICK\n\n• Applications\n\n• Demo\n\nSpeaker: Piyush Santwani - Senior Developer @ BookMyShow\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n3) Webpack - Core Concepts including why do we need it\n\nIn this talk I will take you on a deep dive into automation engineering and expose you to some crazy real-world magic hacks that you can pull off in your full stack JavaScript project’s configuration.\n\nSpeaker: Manjula Dube - Senior Developer @ BookMyShow\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n4) Introduction to Typescript\n\nSpeaker: Gandhali - Sr Tech Evangelist @ Microsoft\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n5) React Fundamentals\n\n• What is react\n\n-- Why React, What problems does React solve\n\n-- React is not just another framework\n\n• React concepts and terminology\n\n-- Components, Virtual DOM, Props, State\n\n• Core of React\n\n-- React.render, React.DOM\n\nSpeakers: Rupesh Mishra - Developer @ Visible Alpha\n\nAnkita Masand - Developer @ BookMyShow\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n6) Intro to GraphQL Lightning talk - 20 mins\n\n• What is GraphQL?\n\n• GraphQL vs Res\n\n• Quick Demo - what GraphQL looks like?\n\n• Code examples with React\n\n• Bonus: using the graphcool app\n\nSpeaker: Amit Erandole (Senior Engineer & Public Speaker)\n\nWrite to me at dube.manjula668[at]gmail[dot]com for any queries\n\nCODE OF CONDUCT\n\nIf we find someone abusing or disrespecting the organizers, speakers or audience. We hold the right to ask that person to leave the workshop & community. We won't think once before blocking that person.",
